HEADWORD: Galactometer
<hw>Gal`ac*tom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/,
<?/, milk + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F. <ets>galactom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.
Cf. <er>Lactometer</er>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for ascertaining the
quality of milk (<it>i.e.</it>, its richness in cream) by determining
its specific gravity; a lactometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

